         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, ¶ 25/9/75. ¶ The honorable the Chief Secretary. ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ I have the honor to seek your permission of proceeding for a few days to the Murray River and the adjacent country, where I intend...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">75.09.25</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Graham Berry</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">H75/11122, unit 816, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">25/9/75.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The honorable the Chief Secretary.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to seek your permission of proceeding for a few days to the Murray River and the adjacent country, where I intend to examine the early spring vegetation before it dries up. Altho' I commenced my travels on the Murray in 1848, I am as yet unacquainted with many of the plants which appear very early in the season, and with their geographic range, altho' such information is required for completing my<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">in place of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>such<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>deleted.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>works. I should need, for the sake of instituting comparisons, to penetrate into a small portion of New South Wales Territory.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">MEL has</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">specimens collected on this trip from Edward River, a long anabranch of the Murray River</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>within NSW</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>If this proposition should meet with your favorable consideration, then I have the honor to request, that a free pass may be granted me by the honorable the Minister of railways for the Echuca line.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 27 September 1875 the Under Secretary, W. Odgers, wrote to the Secretary for Railways: 'Please let [Mueller] have a pass for […] […]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">fpr</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Govt Botanist who is [travelling] on Official duty to the […] [<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">3? words]</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for the Dept […] to free travelling'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">[check this at PRO, p/c rather faint.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">[date unclear, check at PRO]</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[J] Steavenson, Secretary, replied by telegram: 'Passes never issued to Govt. Officers fares must by paid in usual way'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 29 September 1875 Graham Berry, Colonial Secretary wrote to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">J. Steavenson</seg>: 'Baron Mueller [requires] to proceed to the Murray on public business will you supply him with a railway pass. I will explain the matter […] when I see you.'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #FF0000; ">Was this really to Steavenson and not the Commissioner</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #FF0000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of Railways &amp; Roads at this date John Woods.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 30 September 1875 J. Steavenson replied: 'The Commissioner of Railways &amp; Roads directs me to forward a pass (enclosed) because it is asked by the Honorable the Chief Secretary. But he desires me to add that it is entirely contrary to the practice of the Department, and will probably lead to embarrassment in dealing with similar requests.'</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">M had received a free pass to Albury for his journey in January 1874</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">,</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>see M to J. Francis, 24 December 1873 (in this edition as 73-12-24a)</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and notes thereto, but was refused one requested to travel to Ballarat in February 1874, see M to J. Francis, 5 February 1874 (in this edition as 74-02-05a) and W. Odgers to M, 12 February 1874 (in this edition as 74-02-12b).</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I shall remain in daily communication with my office and be able direct the work there from the country.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir, your obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">M to W. Odgers, 3 October 1875</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">,</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>conveyed his<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">t</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">hanks for the pass, and announced he wo</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">uld leave the next day. His return was reported in M to W. Odgers, 14 October 1875</seg>.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">Attached to this file is an undated letter from M:</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
                        xml:lang="en">Sunday</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Please, dear Mr Odgers, convey to the the honor. Grah. Berry my best thanks for his kindness of granting the Railway pass. I shall start to morrow.</p>
                     <p rend="valediction"
                        style="margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">With best regards</p>
                     <p rend="valediction"
                        style="margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="hyphenate: false; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[H75/11122, unit 817, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, PROV.]</p>
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-size: 9pt; ">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 9pt; ">check date of Sunday after this correspondence to get a date - transfer to a letter of its own then?</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
